commit_message:
Revert "Initial heat REST API tests with gabbi"

New non-tempest tests have been added in the heat_integrationtests
directory. They breaks the heat tempest plugin and all gate that enable
heat and run tempest plugins.

This is due to usage heat_integrationtests.common.config.CONF during
load_tests. CONF is not yet populated and still None.

backtrace when running in tempest "tox -eall-plugin"

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/unittest2/loader.py", line 147, in loadTestsFromModule
    return load_tests(self, tests, pattern)
  File "/opt/stack/new/heat/heat_integrationtests/api/test_heat_api.py", line 33, in load_tests
    manager = clients.ClientManager(conf)
  File "/opt/stack/new/heat/heat_integrationtests/common/clients.py", line 74, in __init__
    if self.conf.auth_url.find('/v'):
AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'find'

This reverts commit 172fe35ecebfc55bd425b3c91f3073dac433c018.

Change-Id: Iebc11778353d21ae3723331680c1f663f9a2aeec

commit_message:
Empty /etc/sysconfig/iptables if purge is true and it contains the stock iptables rules

Due to https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1657108 and
https://tickets.puppetlabs.com/browse/MODULES-3184 purging does not work
if /etc/sysconfig/iptables is populated and the iptables service is
stopped. So wo empty the iptables file *only* if it contains the stock
rules contained in the iptables package. The content of this file has
not changed since its inception, so grepping for the string should be
moderately safe. The LP bug contains the full background about this
issue. This approach implements proposal E) as described in the bug.

Change-Id: I94f083a6fee75c5f3015ae32715377061fdead2d
Partial-Bug: #1657108

commit_message:
Change PurgeFirewall default value to true

In order to fix LP bug 1657108 we need to make sure that two
things happen:
1) The stock rpm-shipped /etc/sysconfig/iptables file is emptied
2) That purge firewall rules is true

This change takes care of 2) whereas the depends on takes care of 1).

Change-Id: I34d27ac84b8975c11ec37f54f5d89421ced8581c
Depends-On: I94f083a6fee75c5f3015ae32715377061fdead2d
Partial-Bug: #1657108

commit_message:
libvirt: remove hack for dom.vcpus() returning None

Nova long ago added a workaround for a bug in libvirt
python bindings 0.9.x which would return None instead
of raising an exception when querying vCPUs in some
cases:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1294509

Nova now requires libvirt >= 1.2.1, so will not ever
hit this problem anymore.

Change-Id: I81b07720cf8c7a178b42a048dbac695b1e3db804

commit_message:
Fix ``exportfs -u`` usage in generic driver.

When the generic driver extends or shrinks a share it disables access
to the share by removing its export.  Currently it uses the command
``exportfs -u local_path`` to do so, but this fails with current nfs
packages.

Fix the error by calling ``exportfs -u host:local_path`` instead.

Change-Id: Ic489a1607bf82964bf2859e89b3da1f572436d17
Closes-Bug: #1649782

commit_message:
tests: remove useless variables in db_utils methods

manila/tests/db_utils contains create_share_instance() and
create_share_replica() methods, echo which creates a local
dictionary, updates it from kwargs, and then does nothing
with it.  pep doesn't detect the useless local dictionary
as an unused variable because of the update.

Remove these useless variables.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I6e3a57ddaabfcd77489d5dd6bda369356ff01627

commit_message:
TLS everywhere job introduction

This introduces a job that deploys TLS everywhere (or at least what's
been developed so far).

It's an OVB job with a suffix of fakeha-caserver.

fakeha indicates that it deploys pacemaker (with network isolation),
but I labelled it as fake since it's only one controller, and not 3.

caserver indicates that this job also deploys a CA server, which in
this case is FreeIPA.

FreeIPA is deployed in an extra OVB node, using OVB's undercloud
environment; which means that this node is available when we get an
environment.

HAProxy is using TLS on all endpoints (both public and internal), and
so are most of the services (which are in the internal network).
The certificates they use are provided via certmonoger, which
requests them from FreeIPA. To do this, the nodes need to enroll,
and to do this, I have prepared a script that runs in the NodeTLSCAData
of the nodes that does the enrollment. This method of enrollment will
be replaced by a more automated approach (either via mistral or via
the novajoin vendordata plugin for nova).

Right now, this gate is running on the experimental queue, however,
the plan is to introduce it as a periodic job.

bp tls-via-certmonger

commit_message:
Create and propogate the DSTOOLS_VERSION

devstack-tools will be used to do local.conf manipulation, however we
need a sane way to synchronize the version in the event of a
breakage. This creates a d-g master variable and pushes that out to
all stack.sh and grenade.sh calls

Change-Id: I426295baec4f639b0846e9e2d59c36f9bf997b67

commit_message:
DVR: Fix IPtables driver for metering with DVR routers

IPTables driver for metering was not handling the DVR router
namespaces properly for configuring the metering forward rules.

This patch addresses the issue by configuring the iptables
manager based on the availability of the namespace and selecting
the respective namespaces such as router namespace and snat
namespace with the right external device.

Change-Id: I6790d6ff42d9f8fa220e1a231ae94cbf8b60506c
Closes-Bug: #1506567

commit_message:
Have qos object increment port/network revision

When associate/disassociate qos of port/network, port/network's revision
number will not bump. This patch fixes that.

Conflicts:
	neutron/tests/unit/services/revisions/test_revision_plugin.py
